# Implementation Plan - PISTON MVP

PISTON is a gamified automotive reputation platform where users compete for Garage Reputation (GR). This plan details the creation of the Phase 1 MVP.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Firebase Config & Mock Mode**: To ensure the project is immediately runnable and testable, the database and authentication layer will support a **Mock Mode** (using LocalStorage) if Firebase configuration variables are not set in the `.env` file. Once you provide the Firebase credentials, it will seamlessly switch to the real Firebase services.
> Please review and confirm if this dual-mode design meets your development workflow needs.

> [!TIP]
> **Scoring Engine Customization**: The GR score calculation uses specific weighted inputs. Below is the proposed model. Let us know if you would like to adjust these default values:
> - **Vehicle Rarity**: Multiplier based on tier (Common: 1x, Uncommon: 1.2x, Rare: 1.5x, Exotic: 2.0x, Hypercar: 3.0x).
> - **Estimated Value**: Logarithmic score: `Math.floor(Math.log10(value) * 1000)` (e.g., $10k value = ~4000 pts, $100k value = ~5000 pts).
> - **Build Quality**: Self-assessed or peer-reviewed grade (1 to 10) × 250 points.
> - **Modification Level**: Number of modifications × 150 points.
> - **Verification Status**: Verified vehicles receive a flat +1500 GR bonus.

